t.com/images/2026/06/07/magazine/07mag-ididit-sleep/07mag-ididit-sleep-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Photo illustration by Hannah Whitaker</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Anthropic Files to Go Public, Setting Stage for Huge I.P.O.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/anthropic-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/anthropic-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/anthropic-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The artificial intelligence company, which is racing OpenAI to the stock market, has seen explosive growth over the last year thanks largely to technology that can automatically write computer code.</description><dc:creator>Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 16:04:18 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">IPO</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Dario Amodei</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/21/multimedia/00biz-anthropic-ipo-hfo-jfkm/00biz-anthropic-ipo-hfo-jfkm-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jason Henry for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Anthropic is one of the high-profile tech companies preparing to go public this year.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Chinese Military Sought Nvidia Chips for Years, Report Says</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/business/economy/china-military-nvidia-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/business/economy/china-military-nvidia-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/business/economy/china-military-nvidia-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>An analysis of six years of procurement records suggests that the People’s Liberation Army has openly tried to acquire restricted U.S. technology.</description><dc:creator>Ana Swanson and Tripp Mickle</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 09:02:12 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">NVIDIA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">People's Liberation Army</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Huawei Technologies</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jamestown Foundation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/01/multimedia/01dc-nvidia-china-1-kzlj/01dc-nvidia-china-1-kzlj-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Maxim Shemetov/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>China’s military has stepped up its efforts to acquire artificial intelligence chips despite U.S. restrictions, according to Wirescreen, a software platform.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Peter G. Neumann, Who Warned of Computer Security Risks, Dies at 93</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>For decades, he criticized the industry’s lax attitudes toward computer security and individual digital privacy. He also developed solutions.</description><dc:creator>John Markoff</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 21:27:18 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Peter G Neumann</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DARPA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SRI International</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/24/multimedia/00neumann-kjbp-print1/00neumann-kjbp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jim Wilson/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Peter G. Neumann in 2012. At his death, he was still working full time on advanced computer security design being adopted by companies like Google and Microsoft.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>SpaceX IPO to Be Largest Ever at $135 Share Price</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/technology/spacex-ipo-pricing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/technology/spacex-ipo-pricing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/technology/spacex-ipo-pricing.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The $135 share price means Elon Musk’s rocket maker is poised to exceed the 2019 initial public offering of Saudi Aramco in both valuation and money raised.</description><dc:creator>Ryan Mac</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 22:03:21 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">IPO</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Satellite</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Private spaceflight</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Space</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Stocks</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Bonds</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/02/multimedia/00Biz-SpaceX-Range-ktfb/00Biz-SpaceX-Range-ktfb-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Eric Gay/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>SpaceX’s Starship rocket lifted off last month during a test flight from Starbase in Texas.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>How Box Created 13 New Types of Jobs Because of A.I.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/box-13-new-types-jobs-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/box-13-new-types-jobs-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/technology/box-13-new-types-jobs-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Box, a Silicon Valley software maker, expects to have more employees, not fewer, as it hires A.I. architects, A.I. solutions managers and other new A.I.-related positions.</description><dc:creator>Kalley Huang</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 14:14:19 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Job Recruiting and Hiring</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jobs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Productivity</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Layoffs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Furloughs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">B